      "Item": {
        "Title": "Natalya Bondarchuk",
        "Type": "Interview",
        "Description": "Actress Natalya Bondarchuk, the daughter of Soviet film director Sergei Bondarchuk (War and Peace), went on to act in dozens of feature films after Solaris, but in this interview, she says Hari was her favorite role. Not yet nineteen at the time of production, Bondarchuk was Andrei Tarkovsky\u0027s favorite of the film\u0027s actors. He wrote in his diary, \u0022Natasha B. has outshone everybody.\u0022",
        "Chapters": []
      },
