      "Item": {
        "Title": "Stanislaw Lem",
        "Type": "Short",
        "Description": "One person who decidedly did not like Andrei Tarkovsky\u0027s film was Stanislaw Lem, the author of the source novel. Though similar in plot to the book, the film explores completey different themes from Lem\u0027s philosophically oriented science fiction. This excerpt from a Polish television documentary discusses the best-selling novel and addresses Lem\u0027s attempts to come to some sort of compromise with the intransigent director.",
